he floor but can also be awkwardly placed on a single wall popular in the 90s.";i:16;s:127:"When you have a chair rail it can be hard to figure out whether to use the SAME paint colour on the upper and lower portion of.";i:17;s:227:"A dado rail chair rail or surbase is a practical and decorative moulding that spans the perimeter of a wall with the beneficial purpose of wall protection and aesthetic objective of creating a pleasing visual break for the eye.";i:18;s:162:"Dado rails were installed for more practical purposes in older homes where mouldings such as wainscoting were fitted to disguise rising damp in the walls or as a.";i:19;s:63:"Jan 4 2019 - Explore CHAIR RAILs board Chair Rail on Pinterest.";i:20;s:56:"See more ideas about chair rail wainscoting styles home.";i:21;s:65:"Chair rail is a popular wood trim used today in new construction.";i:22;s:111:"Typically chair rail is between 2 and 3 inches in height and is placed between 32 and 36 inches from the floor.";i:23;s:54:"50 Pictures and Ideas for Chair Rail Molding Projects.";i:24;s:90:"When building refurbishing or just upgrading ones house a whole lot can be ignored in the.";i:25;s:172:"Where the former is concerned these top 70 best chair rail ideas and molding designs help to prevent scuffing along the walls caused by furniture and careless foot traffic.";i:26;s:167:"In the case of the latter chair rail molding establishes an interiors proportion and scale adding space and elegance to otherwise standard straight-up-and-down spaces.";i:27;s:102:"A chair rail is placed at chair height to prevent damage to the wall surface from the backs of chairs.";i:28;s:130:"This moulding can also be installed for purely aesthetic purposes such as to finish the top edge of wainscoting or wall panelling.";i:29;s:92:"Picture rails are perfect for hanging artwork or can simply be used as a decorative feature.";i:30;s:52:"Chair Rail Molding Ideas and Pictures for your Home.";i:31;s:114:"The addition of chair rails adds an interesting design feature to your room creating a refined feel to your space.";i:32;s:161:"Originally used to protect your walls from the movement of chairs they have now become a primary feature in dining rooms living rooms and even bathroom remodels.";i:33;s:95:"Chair and picture rails are interior mouldings that have both functional and decorative appeal.";i:34;s:149:"The chair rail creates a buffer between the walls finish and the chairs posts so the backs of chairs or other furniture dont damage the wall surface.";i:35;s:82:"For aesthetic purposes a chair rail can cover the top edge of wainscoting or wall.";i:36;s:34:"Tips to Add Picture Frame Molding.";i:37;s:103:"With the chair rail up it was time to focus on the bottom portion of the wallthe picture frame molding.";i:38;s:77:"This is where I really needed Finns help well at least his mighty math brain.";i:39;s:25:"Okay lets dive into this.";i:40;s:77:"Oct 28 2015 - Explore Bobbi Jo Thompsons board Chair Rail Ideas on Pinterest.";i:41;s:53:"See more ideas about chair rail home home remodeling.";i:42;s:72:"Browse 3357 professional chair rail stock photos available royalty-free.";i:43;s:57:"Orange painted wall with a light blue painted chair rail.";i:44;s:20:"Chair Rail and Jazz.";i:45;s:141:"Weather Worn Red Yellow Blue and Green Metal Chairs Hang from a Black Cast Iron Hand Rail in Front of a Lime Green Brick Wall Next to a Pink.";i:46;s:96:"People often paint the chair rail molding and the area below it white or a contrast paint color.";i:47;s:137:"The problem with this is that it can tend to cut the room in half or make the room look chopped up and can make your ceilings feel lower.";i:48;s:96:"Below is an example of what it can look like if the trim is painted the same color as the walls.";i:49;s:103:"A chair rail protects the wall from damage caused by the backs of chairs being pushed against the wall.";i:50;s:165:"It takes the form of a horizontal strip of decorative wood fixed at the same height as the chair backs so that the wood rather than the plasterwork takes the knocks.";i:51;s:115:"The method of claim 1 wherein the chair rail is attached between approximately 1 inch and 60 inches from the floor.";i:52;s:131:"The method of claim 1 wherein the chair rail further comprises at least one transparent panel aligned with the at lest one opening.";i:53;s:80:"The method of claim 1 further comprising a cover attached to the elongated body.";i:54;s:163:"About Press Copyright Contact us Creators Advertise Developers Terms Privacy Policy Safety How YouTube works Test new features Press Copyright Contact us Creators.";}}